properties.Description: Properties to create a Source Control Configuration resource

operatorNamespace.Description: The namespace to which this operator is installed to. Maximum of 253 lower case alphanumeric characters, hyphen and period only.

operatorInstanceName.Description: Instance name of the operator - identifying the specific configuration.

operatorParams.Description: Any Parameters for the Operator instance in string format.

configurationProtectedSettings.Description: Name-value pairs of protected configuration settings for the configuration

operatorScope.Description: Scope at which the operator will be installed.

repositoryPublicKey.Description: Public Key associated with this SourceControl configuration (either generated within the cluster or provided by the user).

sshKnownHostsContents.Description: Base64-encoded known_hosts contents containing public SSH keys required to access private Git instances

enableHelmOperator.Description: Option to enable Helm Operator for this git configuration.

provisioningState.Description: The provisioning state of the resource provider.

chartVersion.Description: Version of the operator Helm chart.

chartValues.Description: Values override for the operator Helm chart.

complianceState.Description: The compliance state of the configuration.

lastConfigApplied.Description: Datetime the configuration was last applied.

message.Description: Message from when the configuration was applied.

createdBy.Description: A string identifier for the identity that created the resource

createdByType.Description: The type of identity that created the resource: user, application, managedIdentity, key

lastModifiedBy.Description: A string identifier for the identity that last modified the resource

lastModifiedByType.Description: The type of identity that last modified the resource: user, application, managedIdentity, key

lastModifiedAt.Description: The timestamp of resource last modification (UTC)

properties.Description: Properties of an Extension Instance resource

extensionType.Description: Type of the Extension, of which this resource is an instance of.  It must be one of the Extension Types registered with Microsoft.KubernetesConfiguration by the Extension publisher.

autoUpgradeMinorVersion.Description: Flag to note if this instance participates in auto upgrade of minor version, or not.

releaseTrain.Description: ReleaseTrain this extension instance participates in for auto-upgrade (e.g. Stable, Preview, etc.) - only if autoUpgradeMinorVersion is 'true'.

version.Description: Version of the extension for this extension instance, if it is 'pinned' to a specific version. autoUpgradeMinorVersion must be 'false'.

scope.Description: Scope at which the extension instance is installed.

configurationSettings.Description: Configuration settings, as name-value pairs for configuring this instance of the extension.

configurationProtectedSettings.Description: Configuration settings that are sensitive, as name-value pairs for configuring this instance of the extension.

installState.Description: Status of installation of this instance of the extension.

statuses.Description: Status from this instance of the extension.

creationTime.Description: DateLiteral (per ISO8601) noting the time the resource was created by the client (user).

lastModifiedTime.Description: DateLiteral (per ISO8601) noting the time the resource was modified by the client (user).

lastStatusTime.Description: DateLiteral (per ISO8601) noting the time of last status from the agent.

errorInfo.Description: Error information from the Agent - e.g. errors during installation.

cluster.Description: Specifies that the scope of the extensionInstance is Cluster

namespace.Description: Specifies that the scope of the extensionInstance is Namespace

releaseNamespace.Description: Namespace where the extension Release must be placed, for a Cluster scoped extensionInstance.  If this namespace does not exist, it will be created

targetNamespace.Description: Namespace where the extensionInstance will be created for an Namespace scoped extensionInstance.  If this namespace does not exist, it will be created

code.Description: Status code provided by the Extension

displayStatus.Description: Short description of status of this instance of the extension.

message.Description: Detailed message of the status from the Extension instance.

time.Description: DateLiteral (per ISO8601) noting the time of installation status.

code.Description: Service specific error code which serves as the substatus for the HTTP error code.

principalId.Description: The principal id of the system assigned identity which is used by the configuration.

tenantId.Description: The tenant id of the system assigned identity which is used by the configuration.

type.Description: The type of identity used for the configuration. Type 'SystemAssigned' will use an implicitly created identity. Type 'None' will not use Managed Identity for the configuration.
